{"timestamp": "2026-03-11T18:31:48.605426", "event_type": "command_executed", "source": "router_collect", "data": {"time": "2026-03-11 18:31:48", "input": "start_slsa autonomous learning systems", "response": "Below is a concise \u201cstarter kit\u201d for building, deploying and continuously improving an **autonomous learning system** (ALS) that is **SLSA-compliant**\u2014i.e., it meets the **Supply-chain Levels for Software Artifacts** (SLSA) provenance, integrity and reproducibility standards while still being able to re-train, re-build and re-deploy itself with minimal human touch.\n\n---\n\n### 1. Reference Architecture (10,000 ft view)\n\n```\n\u250c---------------------------\u2510\n\u2502  1. Code & Model Repo     \u2502  \u2190 GitHub/GitLab (protected, signed commits)\n\u2502  2. CI/CD Orchestrator   \u2502  \u2190 GitHub Actions / Tekton / Jenkins w/ SLSA-3+\n\u2502  3. Build & Provenance    \u2502  \u2190 SLSA-3+ provenance (in-toto, cosign, sigstore)\n\u2502  4. Container Registry    \u2502  \u2190 GHCR / GAR / ECR w/ signed images\n\u2502  5. Policy / Admission    \u2502  \u2190 Kyverno / OPA-Gatekeeper checks provenance\n\u2502  6. K8s Runtime           \u2502  \u2190 Autopilot or GKE-Autopilot / EKS / AKS\n\u2502  7. Online Feature Store  \u2502  \u2190 Feast / Vertex AI Feature Store\n\u2502  8. Model Registry        \u2502  \u2190 Vertex AI / MLflow w/ signed model artifacts\n\u2502  9. Auto-Re-train Trigger  \u2502  \u2190 TFX / Vertex Pipelines / Kubeflow Pipelines\n\u2502 10. Canary / Blue-Green   \u2502  \u2190 Argo Rollouts", "source": "brain"}, "correlation_id": "auto", "user_id": null}
